PHASE 08.1 OBJECTIVES:
1. Introduce SQLAlchemy 2.x foundation
2. Add database session lifecycle
3. Add SQLite local/dev support
4. Add PostgreSQL production support
5. Add Alembic migrations
6. Add initial migration
7. Add ORM models scaffold
8. Add repository abstraction layer
9. Preserve existing Phase 01–07 APIs and behavior
10. Keep all tests/builds green

STRICT COMPATIBILITY REQUIREMENTS:
- Existing API routes must continue working unchanged.
- Existing frontend dashboard must continue working unchanged.
- Existing tests must continue passing unchanged.
- Existing agent IDs must remain unchanged.
- Existing response shapes must remain unchanged.
- Existing in-memory behavior may remain temporarily behind repositories.
- Use additive changes only.
- No breaking API changes.

IMPLEMENTATION STRATEGY:
- Add database layer without forcing immediate ORM migration.
- Create repository adapters/shims that preserve current service behavior.
- Use dependency-injected DB session pattern.
- SQLite default for dev/tests.
- PostgreSQL configurable via env.
- Alembic must support future migrations cleanly.
- Models should include at minimum:
  - users
  - roles
  - audit_logs
  - sessions (optional scaffold)
- Audit persistence may be scaffold-only in 08.1.
- Do not yet enforce auth.

RECOMMENDED BACKEND STRUCTURE:
backend/app/db/
  base.py
  session.py
  models/
  repositories/
  migrations/

EXPECTED CONFIG ADDITIONS:
- DATABASE_URL
- DB_ECHO
- DB_POOL_SIZE
- DB_MAX_OVERFLOW

SAFE DEFAULTS:
- local/dev:
    sqlite:///./zdash.db
- production:
    require explicit PostgreSQL DATABASE_URL

PRODUCTION SAFETY:
- Reject default JWT secrets in production mode.
- Reject default admin passwords in production mode.
- Fail safely when production secrets missing.

DO NOT:
- globally require database before compatibility layer exists
- rewrite all services directly to ORM
- force PostgreSQL locally
- break tests
- rename routes
- rename API response fields
- change frontend API assumptions

